   "source": [
    "# Interview Prep: 22 - Staff Engineering & Leadership\n",
    "\n",
    "At the Staff level, you are no longer just a \"coder\". You are a **Technical Leader**. This notebook covers the soft skills, strategic processes, and leadership philosophies required to influence an entire organization.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. The RFC Process (Technical Strategy)\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Interview Question**: \"How do you align three different teams on a single technical direction when they all have different opinions?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Answer**: You use the **RFC (Request for Comments)** process.\n",
    "1. **Draft**: You write a clear document outlining the Problem, Proposed Solution, and Rejected Alternatives.\n",
    "2. **Gather Feedback**: Circulate it to key stakeholders (Engineers, PMs, Security).\n",
    "3. **Iterate**: Addressing concerns in the document creates a paper trail of why decisions were made.\n",
    "4. **Seal**: Once consensus is reached, the RFC becomes the "Source of Truth" for the project. \n",
    "\n",
    "**Staff Tip**: Acknowledge that architecture is a social process. If the teams aren't aligned, the best tech stack in the world will fail.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Managing Technical Debt\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Interview Question**: \"How do you convince a Product Manager to stop building features and focus on technical debt?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Answer**: Translate tech debt into **Business Risk** and **Developer Velocity**.\n",
    "- Don't say: \"The code is messy and needs refactoring.\"\n",
    "- Say: \"Currently, adding a new payment method takes 4 weeks because of the legacy billing layer. If we invest 2 weeks in refactoring, we can reduce future feature delivery time to 3 days and prevent a critical outage risk.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Influence Without Authority\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Interview Question**: \"Tell me about a time you had to mentor a senior engineer who didn't report to you.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Focus**: Cross-team impact. \n",
    "- Focus on **Review**, **RFC Feedback**, and **Knowledge Sharing**.\n",
    "- Explain how you identified a gap in their approach (e.g., lack of observability) and guided them to the solution through questioning rather than dictating.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Case Study: The First 30 Days of a Migration\n",
    "\n",
    "**Scenario**: You are hired to lead the migration of a failing Python monolith to a distributed microservice architecture. \n",
    "\n",
    "**Your Plan**:\n",
    "1. **Audit (Week 1)**: Map the dependencies. Which part of the monolith is the most fragile? (The "Strangler Fig" pattern start).\n",
    "2. **Proof of Concept (Week 2)**: Migrate one small, low-risk service (e.g., Notification service) to prove the pipeline and pattern.\n",
    "3. **Standards (Week 3)**: Define the shared standards for all future services (Auth, Logging, Retries).\n",
    "4. **Enablement (Week 4)**: Create a CLI or template so other teams can follow your pattern without hand-holding.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Staff Engineering Artifacts\n",
    "- **ADRs (Architecture Decision Records)**: Short documents explaining *why* a specific decision was made at a point in time.\n",
    "- **Incident Post-Mortems**: Blameless reviews of what went wrong and how to fix the *system*, not the person.\n",
    "---"
   ]
  }
